headlines.description: — Returning to the bench for the first time in 10 months, Quin Snyder quickly got an idea of the challenge he faces with the Atlanta Hawks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal, Wizards spoil Snyder's Hawks debut with 119-116 win

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 33 points and 15 rebounds, and the Milwaukee Bucks extended their winning streak to 15 games by beating the Brooklyn Nets 118-104 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis returns, Bucks beat Nets 118-104 for 15th straight

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 20 points, Gary Trent Jr. had 19 and the Toronto Raptors beat the Chicago Bulls 104-98 on Tuesday night for their eighth victory in 10 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors beat Bulls 104-98 for 8th victory in 10 games

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 28 of his 39 points in the third quarter and added 10 assists and 10 rebounds, and the Memphis Grizzlies beat Los Angeles 121-109 on Tuesday night in the Lakers' first game since LeBron James injured his right foot.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant's third-quarter burst leads Grizzlies past Lakers

headlines.description: — When Nikola Jokic was presented with the game ball by Denver coach Michael Malone after recording his 100th career triple-double, Malone said the superstar seemed almost embarrassed by the gesture.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has 100th triple-double; Nuggets down Rockets 133-112

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes scored 29 points and the Sacramento Kings beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 123-117 on Tuesday night for their fourth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnes scores 29 points, Kings beat Thunder for 4th straight

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton gets to celebrate twice after winning a duel of birthday boys with Luka Doncic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton scores 32, Pacers hold off Doncic, Mavs, 124-122

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Keldon Johnson scored 25 points and the San Antonio Spurs snapped a 16-game losing streak, beating the Utah Jazz 102-94 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs snap 16-game losing streak with victory over Jazz

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — The goal for Golden State: Do everything to shut down Damian Lillard, without fouling the Trail Blazers star after he made all 16 of his free throws last time against the defending champs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole, Thompson rally Warriors back to beat Blazers 123-105

headlines.description: — Jaden McDaniels isn't the first player that comes to mind when mentioning key players on the Minnesota Timberwolves' roster, but the forward is proving to be a problem for the Los Angeles Clippers.
headlines.shortLinkText: McDaniels has 20 points, Timberwolves beat Clippers 108-101
